Module org.nasdanika.graph
Package org.nasdanika.graph.processor

Interface ProcessorFactory<P,​H,​E>

  • Type Parameters:
    P - Processor type - what is passed to parent/child processors and also returned to the client code to interact with the processor network. For model elements which are not interacted with by other processors or the client code the result may be null.
    H - Handler type. Handlers are invoked by endpoints.
    E - Endpoint type. Endpoints pass invocations to handlers.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Composeable<ProcessorFactory<P,​H,​E>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    NopEndpointProcessorFactory<P,​H>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractEObjectFactory, DrawioEObjectFactory, NopEndpointReflectiveProcessorFactory, PropertySourceEObjectFactory, ReflectiveProcessorFactory, ResourceSetPropertySourceEObjectFactory
    public interface ProcessorFactory<P,​H,​E>
extends Composeable<ProcessorFactory<P,​H,​E>>
    Processor factory creates and "wires" processors.
    Author:
    Pavel
